Stenoptinea is a genus of the fungus moth family, Tineidae. Therein, it belongs to the subfamily Meessiinae. It was originally established as a subgenus of Homosetia, but later separated to become a genus in its own right.Only three species are placed in Stenoptinea at present:
Stenoptinea auriferella (Dietz, 1905)
Stenoptinea cyaneimarmorella (Milli√®re, 1854) (= S. angustipennis)
Stenoptinea ornatella (Dietz, 1905)